{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Goat's Cheese Flans and Leeks","content":["Grease and flour 4 heatproof ramekins (approx. Ø 9 cm, height 5 cm) and set aside.","Place milk, goat's cheese, flour and salt in mixing bowl and mix <b>30 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add egg yolks and mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl and lid thoroughly."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Place egg whites in mixing bowl and whisk <b>2 min\/speed 3<b> or until stiff.","Add reserved egg yolk mixture and whisk <b>30 sec\/speed 1.5<b>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Transfer to prepared ramekins, arrange in Varoma dish and set aside. Clean mixing bowl.","Place water in mixing bowl. Insert simmering basket and add leeks and red peppers to it. Set Varoma containing ramekins in position and steam <b>18 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Set covered Varoma aside on a plate to keep flans warm. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and set aside. Empty and clean mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Yoghurt Sauce","content":["Place goat’s cheese, plain yoghurt, chives, salt and black pepper in mixing bowl and mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Adjust seasoning to taste.","Unmould flans by running a small thin knife around inside edge of each ramekin, then invert onto a plate, carefully helping flan out of ramekin with knife if necessary. Arrange steamed leeks and red peppers around flans, drizzle with sauce and serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Goat's Cheese Flans and Leeks","content":["butter, for greasing","40 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","130 g milk","140 g soft goat's cheese","½ tsp salt","2 eggs, separated","500 g water","300 g leeks, white part only, sliced (5 mm)","50 g red peppers, diced (1 cm)"]},{"title":"Yoghurt Sauce","content":["60 g soft goat's cheese","125 g plain yoghurt","6 fresh chives, chopped","2 - 3 pinches salt","2 pinches ground black pepper, or to taste"]}],"id":"r150825","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blog